latestPosts.caption:
HAPPY HOUR WITH CHICA 🩺♥️

I was listening for the past decade. I listened, I acknowledged, and I crafted. 

Fully diving into my witchcraft of helping people feel seen, heard and uplifted and ready to slam the negative wiring(s) outta your system. I'm here to remind you that the hustle culture has very gradually made you believe that self care practices are a waste of time or even narcissistic. And that's a BLOCKER to address asap. You have ONE life. And your sole purpose is always to care of your system first. 

You're human. Not a machine. 

"Pampered, overindulged, self care junkie" are words often thrown at people who enjoy the good things in life and who are not afraid to show it. To think about it, the Internet or people in general only cater to the surface level information, but only YOU know the "whys" behind your "how's" . People waste so much time trying to crack the "WHY" behind someone who seems happy and bubbly, but they barely want to do the extra work to break down the "HOW" of it all. And that's where your initiative makes all the difference. 

I'm here to remind you, that there is nothing wrong with addressing your own needs and ensuring that they are met. 

🔗Click the link in my bio for booking a time slot🔗

latestPosts.caption:
Happy Hour with Chica: an initiative for well-being, connectivity and more life💌

"Performative self care is the first step towards opening the door for transformative self care" - Marie Bruce.

Performative self-care is great for an immediate boost to your mood, or for building up several simple tasks into a solid routine. Because let's face it, there are times in life when a simple task is all that you can manage. You might have recently experienced loss, or are undergoing heavy transformative episodes and at such times, going deeper might get overwhelming, so the surface level self-care i.e. performative practices is what's most valuable during such difficult times 🔖

Long story short, I'm sure you've heard about my journey. I explored, I failed, I switched and now I've come to a decision. I've finally decided to utilise my education and my brand around altruism and energy to do what I'm best at; catering towards better mental health.  After years of grinding, confusion, and soul searching, I finally feel like I'm on the right path. I'm finally in sync with all my skills to launch this project that is so close to my heart and soul. Turning 30 this year and I've been having this deep ache in my heart to turn my wisdom from my life journey and my drive of wanting to help people, into something more substantial. 

Happy hour with Chica is my baby. Is my heart. It's something that I've always wanted to do, and have managed to do all my life but I'm finally ready to turn it into a force. A motion. 

Thankful for this digital era, for I can now connect with my audience from all across the globe: from India, to USA, to UK, to Canada. It's always been about that international love♥️ 

I hope you see it, for what it is. And I hope you dive into this journey of enjoying life, with me 💕

Happy Hour with Chica now available on my LinkTree. 
Book through Calendly 📤📮

🎥 @lilrem_filmmaker

latestPosts.caption:
Just a girl with a heart & some dreams 🕊️🖤

I look back and think about how far I've come in being my unapologetic self. It didn't always start that way, but I tapped into it quite early on. The sooner you realise that outside noises are only distractions that are sent your way to test your resilience and will power, the easier it gets to enjoy every part of it. Just set your intention and hold your ground. Cause even if you don't know what you're doing in life (hard relate) the intention saves you from the chaos. 

Sending love to those who feel distracted. 
It all aligns in time🩵
